doc_summary_long: Victoria Cross recipient Johnson Beharry has described his 'humiliation' after being held up by US border officials amid Donald Trump's immigration clampdown. The Iraq war hero arrived at New York's JFK airport hours after the president ordered travel restrictions on nationals from seven mainly Muslim countries on January 27. Beharry, who was seriously injured in the conflict in 2004, said he faced a wait of nearly three hours to reach the border where his passport was further scrutinised.
doc_summary_short: Victoria Cross recipient Johnson Beharry has described his 'humiliation' after being held up by US border officials amid Donald Trump's immigration clampdown.
doc_title: Victoria Cross hero Johnson Beharry left feeling 'humiliated' by US border officials
